television broadcasts? Who should produce them? What kinds of publics are and are not possible through media? How exactly do discourses move into, out of, and through the media to affect everyday social practices? Mixed Messages addresses these questions through a rich ethnography of the Russian Federation's Buryat territories, a multilingual and multiethnic region on the Mongolian border with a complex relationship to both Europe and Asia.Mixed Messages shows that belonging in Asian Russia is a dynamic process that one cannot capture analytically by using straightforward categories of ethnolinguistic identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBuriat languagexPolitical aspects. 0aBuriatsxEthnic identity. 0aEthnic mass mediazRussia (Federation)zBuri︠a︡tii︠a︡. 0aEthnologyzRussia (Federation)zBuri︠a︡tii︠a︡. 0aLanguage policyzRussia (Federation)zBuri︠a︡tii︠a︡. 0aMass media and ethnic relationszRussia (Federation)zBuri︠a︡tii︠a︡. 4aAsian Studies. 4aSoviet & East European History. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aCommunication, Media, linguistics, Russia, Eastern Europe, Language, minorities.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069046008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501750533?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501750533423Coveruhttps://www.d